CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 29, 1955, pg. A8 reads: "NAACP Protest Rally: 3,000 Hear Emmett Till Case Facts; Give; Urge United States to Act - Receives Orchids - Mrs. T.R.M. Howard receives orchids from Mrs. Robert L. Vann, Courier president and treasurer, in behalf of the Pittsburgh Branch of the NAACP."
TitMainTitle: Jessie Vann pinning corsage onto Helen Howard, at Soldier's and Sailor's Memorial Hall for NAACP protest rally
